the most significant bits of data byte 4 signify what data follows.
If bit 1(0x10) is set, then zoom data follows
if bit 2(but not bit 1) is set, then 2 bytes of zoom data follows
if bit 4 is set, then 2 bytes of rotate data follows

example from above data:

0c 61 81 f0 90 00 10 ae 39 03 79 09 7b

0c 61 81 : is the event code and other stuff
f0 90 00 10 : is the first 4 data bytes. The last byte has bit 0x10 set, so zoom data follows, read 2 bytes
ae 39 : 0x39 has byte 0x20 set, so 2 more bytes of zoom data will follow
03 79 : 0x79 has byte 0x40 set, so 2 bytes of rotation data will follow
09 7b : rotation data

another example:

00 61 81 f0 90 00 30 06 33 04 37

0c 61 81 : again, event code + stuff
f0 90 00 30 : has both bits 0x20 and 0x10 set. In this case bit 0x10 takes precedence and 0x20 is the most significant bit of the next data value (or something)
06 33 : 0x33 has byte 0x20 set, so 2 more bytes of zoom data will follow
04 37 : 0x37 does not have bit 0x40 set, so no rotate data
